(297, 'Draft: Hi team, Sharing the heads-up note for our investment in [Neuralzome Cybernetics](/11f29bccb6fc8040a51cf08cae0cb796). This is a Quickly Teachable Agent platform — allowing users to train equipment or machinery to perform actions or exhibit behaviors. The initial use-case is precision agriculture in the USA. Neuralzome Cybernetics is a spin-out of the AI & Robotics team plus IP from [Flo Mobility](https://flomobility.com/) (a Blume Founder’s Fund portfolio company) DeVC is investing $100K/₹86L as part of a wider ₹12 crore round led by 8X Ventures This is a Venture Partner cheque (via Ashwini) which also meets the DeVC Community Top Up criteria **Founders** 1. [Mohan Shivam](https://www.linkedin.com/in/mohansivam/) — CEO 1. ex CoFo at CTO at Flo Mobility (3 YOE) 1. Ex CoFo at GAMASOME (8.5 YOE) 1. [Aditya Shriwastava](https://www.linkedin.com/in/adish-ai/) — CTO 1. ex head of robotics at Flo Mobility (2 YOE) 1. ex engineer at iFuture Robitics (1.5 YOE) 1. BITS Mera graduate **Investing Process** 1. This was sourced by the DeVC Collective via Soumitra Sharma 1. Cash did the 1PE followed by expert chat (with Peepul Agri founder) 1. From expert chat —  *“Neural is a top notch team | polymath robotics is also doing similar in US, but likely going to be multiple expensive. cost is key here.” * 1. Mohit & DC did a 2PE 1. Per Mohit — *“Spikey 1 with a spike in product and hustle, and resilience.”* 1. Details were surfaced to the full DeVC Collective 1. Ashwini: *“Positives: Fou...'),
